Pre Processor:
#include <library.h>    - Search in /usr/include
#include "library.h"    - Search in current directory or in /usr/include

#define name value  - Define a constant with a value

#ifdef name     - If is defined
#ifndef name    - If is not defined
#else
#endif          - Close conditions


Variables:
type name; or type name = value;
Tip: Don't use extern variables
extern type name    - Global variable(Don't use)
register type name  - Doesn't have a memory address
static type name    - Permanent storage

Conversion:
(type)name

Comments:
// One line
/*
    Multiple lines
*/

Conditions(break exit the switch case):
if(condition){...}
else{...}
(condition) ? iftrue : iffalse

switch(variable){
    case x:
        ...
        break;
    ...
    default:
        ...
        break;
}

Loops(break exit the loop, continue skips to next loop iteration):
for(init; condition; step){...}
while(condition){...}
do{...}while(condition);

Recursion:
BIG POWER BIG RESPONSABILITY

Goto and labels:
DON'T USE THEM

Operators:
+       - Sum
++      - Increment by 1        (n++, first n last n += 1)(++n, first n+=1 last n)
*       - Mult
-       - Substr
--      - Decrement by 1        (n--, first n last n -= 1)(--n, first n-=1 last n)
/       - Div
%       - Modulus
=       - Assign
==      - Equal
!=      - Not equal
< <=    - Lower than or equal
> >=    - Greater than or equal
||      - OR
&&      - AND

Bitwise Operators
&       - AND
|       - OR
^       - XOR
<<      - Left shift
>>      - Right shift
~       - Complement

Characters:
'\0'    - Null
Uses ASCII

Strings:
char[]
Null indicates end of string

Functions (value or reference)
- Prototype:
outputType name(inputType);

- Definition:
outputType name(inputType){...}

Structures:
struct name
{
    ...
}
Optimized version for memory padding
struct __attribute__((packed)) name
{
    higherBits
    ...
    lowerBits
}
typedef struct __attribute((packed))
{
    higherBits
    ...
    lowerBits
}name

